Psuedo Code

Scores are not arrays of chords, but arrays of NoteIntervals

Score moves at a given BPM, easy is slow hard is fast
- For scanned sheet music, allow an option to change the BPM for practice and what not

Each note has an interval depending on its duration

When a note is played, look at the active intervals at that point

If a note overlaps interval in NoteInterval then increase duration played of interval, else add to WrongIntervals
- Have a little buffer at start and end of intervals
- If a note is played before a notes interval but within its buffer, count that note for the buffered note if it doesnt count better for playing for the previous interval
- Duration of a note being played is defined as time from noteOn -> noteOff
- - If a note is played way to early and is wrong, but is held till later then it should be right
- - - Look at all overlapping intervals while the note is on, and if there is one that matches then penalize early and then continue duration
- - - If a note is played early AND wrong then intervals will overlap but note won't
- Dont compare just notes, compare notes that have overlapping intervals

If a wrong note is played during an interval, record when the note was played
- Record the midi and the time of noteOn, which can be rendered later to show an incorrect note

Once song is over, the song of Intervals that started with all now have DurationPlayed values

Score is calculated based on the Duration, Missed notes, Incorrect notes, etc.



